import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    zip_count = data.groupby('state')['zip_code'].count().reset_index()
    zip_count.columns = ['state', 'zip_code_count']
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='state', y='zip_code_count', data=zip_count, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across different states?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Zip Codes')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    chart.legend(title='States', loc='upper right', labels=zip_count['state'].unique())
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='longitude', y='latitude', hue='state', legend='full', palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude values?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.25, 1), title='State')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    zip_county = data.groupby('county')['zip_code'].count().reset_index()
    zip_county = zip_county.sort_values('zip_code', ascending=False)

    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='county', y='zip_code', data=zip_county)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of zip codes across different counties?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("County")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Zip Codes")
    plt.legend(title="Counties", loc="upper right", labels=zip_county['county'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    city_zip_counts = data.groupby('city')['zip_code'].nunique().sort_values(ascending=False).head(10)
    chart = sns.barplot(x=city_zip_counts.index, y=city_zip_counts.values)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of zip codes across different cities?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("City")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Zip Codes")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    chart.legend(title="Top 10 Cities")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
